               <head>'Abd al-Qadir Khan, autobiography</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by ʿUmdat al-ʿUlamāʾ Dabīr al-Dawlah Ṣādiq al-Mulk Mawlānā ʿAbd al-Qādir Khān Bahādur S̲ābit Jang</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85010050 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064939 http://lccn.loc.gov/nr92042659" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4049-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alternative" key="person_f7659">ʿUmdat al-ʿUlamāʾ Dabīr al-Dawlah Ṣādiq al-Mulk Mawlānā ʿAbd al-Qādir Khān Bahādur S̲ābit Jang</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7659" type="alternative">عمدة العلماٴ دبير الدّوله صادق الملك مولانا عبد القادر خان بهادر ثابت جنگ</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>No title state in work</p>
                        <p>Author simply identified in text as ʿAbd al-Qādir ibn Muḥammad Akram. However, the author's fuller title is stated only on the title page</p>
                        <p>Autobiography of a late Timurid or Mughal bureaucrat and religious scholar of Ajmer and Jabalpur (b. 24 Z̤ū al-Ḥijjah 1196 / 30 November 1782, at Moradabad)</p>
                        <p>The work appears to have been composed late in the author's life, with the year 1831 being mentioned as "the current year." However, the narrative extends only until 1825</p>
                        <p>Some details, such as the names of European officers are not remembered; Captain James Tod is an exception</p>
                        <p>Numerous digressions on the ʿulamāʾ of Lucknow, Moradabad and its environs, governors of Ajmer, the dargāh of the saint Muʿīn al-Dīn Chishtī, Gond Maharajahs of Jabalpur, and so on</p>
                        <p>Large lacuna in narrative (f. 35r), jumping from 1225 / 1805 to July 1818. Similar lacuna on f. 96v</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
